Lebrely OpenEdX Validation — Licensing

This repository contains two kinds of artefacts, licensed differently:

1. Source code (everything in `scripts/`) — MIT License.
2. Data and reports (everything in `data/`, `predictions/`, `reports/`, plus
   `abstract.md`) — Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
   (CC-BY-4.0). Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

Upstream attribution: `data/openedx_models.json` contains source code
extracted from the Open edX platform (https://github.com/openedx/edx-platform),
which is licensed under AGPL-3.0. That embedded code remains under its
upstream licence; our aggregation and annotation of it is offered under
CC-BY-4.0 for the non-code metadata (table names, app taxonomy, extraction
timestamps).

